080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-00355/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-00355/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-00355/canvas/1/f3f7f03b-b335-4cfb-848b-786062185356","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-07-31T16:27:35.062Z","creator":"Naveah","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This pipe, which aligns perfectly with the area of the screen where Barry was sitting until now, points down to signal and foreshadow the character's trajectory as he sinks into the depth of loneliness.</p><p>In &lt;a href=\"<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" class=\"text-blue-500 underline hover:text-blue-600\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/punc-00321.html&quot;&gt;the\">https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/punc-00321.html\"&gt;the</a> previous shot&lt;/a&gt;, the finger of the hand that holds the phone points upward, also signaling a tension between his sadness (down) and his desire for happiness (up).</p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-00355/canvas/1#xywh=348,372,225,189"},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-00355/canvas/1/9866cbdd-4419-4c05-af63-9148320d9bfe","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2025-07-31T16:28:15.202Z","creator":"Naveah","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Again,&nbsp;even though it is part of a larger moving shot, this is not a traditional way to bring viewers into the film: Barry's head leaves the frame. However, as we get to know him and his story and witness his actions, this temporary framing is congruent with the character and his internal state (he loses his head). As he continues to walk from his desk to the door of the warehouse, he moves from artificial light (pictured) to darkness to bright, natural light, previewing the character's narrative and emotional arc.â€‹</p>"}],"target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/punc/punc-00355/canvas/1#xywh=1017,140,184,147"}]}]}]}